yingyinNormal.en: How to Celebrate Chinese New Year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如何庆祝中国年。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, that's great! Let's go celebrate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真棒，我们去庆祝吧！

yingyinNormal.en: We're here today to celebrate love.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今日我们齐聚一堂来庆祝爱情。

yingyinNormal.en: To celebrate your 30 under 30 thing. Right, Sheldon?
yingyinNormal.zh: 庆祝一下你的大器早成，对吧，谢尔顿？

yingyinNormal.en: Here's how to celebrate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下面看看如何庆祝这个节日。

yingyinNormal.en: Just us, and that's the way I'd like to celebrate it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就我们，我就想这样庆祝。

yingyinNormal.en: No, because we don't celebrate the ancient pagan festival of Saturnalia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，我们不庆祝古老的异教农神节。

yingyinNormal.en: Why not? I don't celebrate my birthday. Shut up. Yeah, you do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么？我不庆祝生日的。开玩笑，你不会的。

yingyinNormal.en: You can also light firecrackers and bang drums and gongs to celebrate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你也可以点一些鞭炮,敲锣打鼓来庆祝。

yingyinNormal.en: We can celebrate the holidays, because they're willing to miss their own.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们能够庆祝这些节日因为他们愿意错过他们自己的度假。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you married, Captain？Jeff, why don't you go take a break？You deserve to celebrate. Sure. Can I get you something？No, I am fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 上尉，你结婚了吗？杰夫，休息一下吧，你该好好庆祝庆祝。当然，要给你带点什么吗？不，不用了。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, I am very disappointed that I won't be able to celebrate Howard's accomplishment tonight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我好失望哦，今晚不能给霍华德庆祝他的成就。

yingyinNormal.en: Thank you very much for coming today to help celebrate our dear friend, James Holt.
yingyinNormal.zh: 非常感谢各位今天的出席共同为我们的朋友詹姆斯·浩特庆祝。

yingyinNormal.en: Why don't we cancel our dinner reservation and the three of us celebrate Valentine's here?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们何不取消晚餐预订，我们三个一起在家里庆祝情人节？

yingyinNormal.en: Me and my husband are going to celebrate together with my parents and my sister and her whole family.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我和丈夫准备一起庆祝，偕同我的父母和妹妹一家。

yingyinNormal.en: Kick ass! Oh, God. We have to celebrate. You know we should do like a soap opera theme.
yingyinNormal.zh: 了不起。敬乔伊。那我们必须要庆祝，应该开个肥皂剧主题派对。

yingyinNormal.en: We're here to celebrate the marriage of Sheldon Lee Cooper and Amy Farrah Fowler.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们欢聚于此一同庆祝谢尔顿·李·库珀与艾米·菲拉·福勒喜结良缘。

yingyinNormal.en: So the divorce, the marriage, we got a lot to celebrate. How about we all go out to dinner tomorrow night.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们要庆祝离婚跟结婚，我们明晚何不一起吃晚餐？

yingyinNormal.en: Anyway, I just ran into Ross and Chandler downstairs, and they think we should go out and celebrate. You know, someplace nice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我认为我们该出去庆祝一下，去个好地方。

yingyinNormal.en: Today is International Day, when we celebrate all the countries of the world. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天有个节日叫国际日，这是一个全世界所有国家共同庆祝的节日。太好啦！

word_usage.usage:
celebrate后面常跟节日、胜利、成功或类似性质的词作宾语，不可以接人，也不接that从句。
示例：How do you celebrate New Year? 
你怎样庆贺新年？

celebrate也可用作不及物动词，作“庆祝”解。
示例：We're going out to celebrate.
我们要外出庆祝一下。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 通常指举行盛大隆重的仪式庆祝或纪念有意义的日子或某件事情, 多暗示节日般的欢乐场面。
指对他人祝贺为目的, 希望他人幸福或走运。

celebrate后面常跟节日、胜利、成功或类似性质的词作宾语，不可以接人，也不接that从句。
示例：How do you celebrate New Year? 
你怎样庆贺新年？

celebrate也可用作不及物动词，作“庆祝”解。
示例：We're going out to celebrate.
我们要外出庆祝一下。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 通常指举行盛大隆重的仪式庆祝或纪念有意义的日子或某件事情，多暗示节日般的欢乐场面。
